. Other essays provide analyses of additional contemporary and historical North American Indigenous foodways while also addressing issues of tradition and cultural change. Scholars and other readers interested in ecology, climate change, world hunger, colonization, religious studies, and cultural studies will find this book to be a valuable resource.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aFoodxNorth AmericaxReligious aspects. 0aFoodzNorth AmericaxReligious aspects. 0aIndians of North AmericaxFood. 0aIndians of North AmericaxReligion. 4aAmerican Studies : Indigenous Studies. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology of Religion. 4aAnthropology and Archaeology : Anthropology. 4aCultural Studies : Food. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / Native American Studies.2bisacsh1 aGross, Lawrence W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKelley, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcnally, Michael D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Brien, Suzanne Crawford, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPesantubbee, Michelene E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPesantubbee, Michelene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aR. Alfred, Vick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSanchez, Andrea Mccomb, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalsh, David S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWogahn, Kimberly, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZogry, Michael J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZogry, Michael J., eeditor.4edt